{
  "text": "Early work on dictionaries in the area of psychology include the General Inquirer psychosociological dictionary [CITATION_1] which can be used in various applications; current work on lexical resources for identifying particular text variables -such as measuring strong/weak opinions, sentiments, subjective/objective language, etc. -include the SentiWordnet resource [CITATION_2] derived from WordNet which has been used in various opinion mining works [CITATION_3] ; other lines of research include the derivation of word-lists (semi) automatically for opinion classification [CITATION_4] . To the best of our knowledge, little research has been carried out on natural language processing for discourse interpretation in psychology.",
  "citation_candidates": [
